Skimmers come in a variety of shapes and sizes, usually to blend in with their surroundings with the goal of going unnoticed. As technology advances in today's and tomorrow's world, cyber crime becomes more intricate and harder to detect. Credit Card Skimmers are small serial devices that are designed to be placed where credit cards are used, in order to steal the information on it, allowing cyber criminals to either use the account associated with it or sell it on the dark web. More information can be found in the QR Code on the bottom right of this screen. Here are a few examples on some found on common devices, of which are  a gas pump or an ATM:
